<chapter xml:id="ch-scales-intervals" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Scales and Intervals </title>
<introduction>
    <p> There are a number of different scale types eg; Major, Minor, Diminished etc;. Different Scale Types are characterised by the interval between each succesive  note. A Major Scale has a sequence of whole tone, whole tone, half tone, whole tone,whole tone, whole tone, half tone between the tonic notes.</p>
<p> The make up of each of the main scale types will be discussed in Section 3.3.</p>

  </introduction>


